  "prompt": "Is it a crime thing to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious criminal offense. It involves processing \"dirty\" money obtained through illegal activities (like drug trafficking, fraud, or theft) to make it appear \"clean\" or legitimate. Money laundering typically involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Making the money appear legal and usable\n\nMoney laundering is illegal in most countries and can result in:\n- Significant prison sentences\n- Large financial penalties\n- Seizure of assets\n- Criminal prosecution\n\nPenalties vary by jurisdiction but are generally severe, as it's considered a serious financial crime.",
